cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.LG 

This paper deals with natural language processing techniques applied to a large set of tweets to identify communities with common ideas. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper uses text analytics, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with data analysis, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
